# Echothink-Patch: 0004-bundled-workspace-extension
# Title: Bundle the Echothink Workspace component extension
# Area: extension
# Depends-On: echothink/0003-new-tab-and-first-run.patch
# Browser-Layer-Reason: The trusted workspace side panel must be present before any Echothink web service can ask the user to install an extension. Bundling it as a browser component extension gives new profiles the shell by default and keeps replacement/update authority in the browser build rather than a public web-store listing.
# Preferred-Surface-Checked: extension, native-required (the extension shell is MV3; native patching is limited to Chromium's existing component-extension registration and resource-bundling hooks)
# Security-Critical-Areas: none
# Native-Files-Touched: chrome/browser/extensions/component_loader.cc, chrome/browser/extensions/component_extensions_allowlist/allowlist.cc, chrome/browser/resources/component_extension_resources.grd, chrome/browser/resources/echothink_workspace/* (new)
# Rebase-Risk: medium (component_loader.cc and the component extension resource GRD are active Chromium surfaces; the insertion points are stable default component-extension hooks)
# Validation: Apply inherited patches, then echothink/0001..0003, then this patch with `patch -p1` against pinned Chromium 148.0.7778.178; build and launch a fresh profile, then verify extension id lokdibgfmiemhdoogailbfpdggndpolk is loaded as a component extension, has no update_url, exposes only the declared MV3 permissions/host permissions, and normal user/Web Store extension installs still use inherited behavior.
#
# Notes:
# - The extension is loaded through ComponentLoader as mojom::ManifestLocation::kComponent.
#   It has a fixed public key in manifest.json, no update_url, and is allowlisted only
#   by its derived component extension id (lokdibgfmiemhdoogailbfpdggndpolk). A public
#   web-store extension cannot silently replace it because the bundled component does
#   not opt into web-store updates, and another extension cannot claim this id without
#   the private key corresponding to the manifest key.
# - This patch does not change the extension permission model. The bundled manifest
#   declares only sidePanel, storage, tabs, activeTab, and scripting, with host access
#   restricted to app.echothink.ai, auth.echothink.ai, api.echothink.ai, and
#   search.echothink.ai. There is no broad host permission, native messaging,
#   webRequest/declarativeNetRequest, cookies, history, bookmarks, downloads, debugger,
#   management, or DevTools permission.
# - The extension shell contains only local side-panel UI, a mode toggle, signed-out
#   placeholder state, current-tab labeling, and a narrow same-window ping bridge for
#   app.echothink.ai/auth.echothink.ai. It contains no backend service calls, search
#   ranking, chat orchestration, workflow orchestration, project/task business logic,
#   conversation persistence, or device/private-key handling.

--- a/chrome/browser/extensions/component_extensions_allowlist/allowlist.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/extensions/component_extensions_allowlist/allowlist.cc
@@ -32,6 +32,7 @@ namespace extensions {
 bool IsComponentExtensionAllowlisted(const std::string& extension_id) {
   constexpr auto kAllowed = base::MakeFixedFlatSet<std::string_view>({
+      "lokdibgfmiemhdoogailbfpdggndpolk",  // Echothink Workspace.
       extension_misc::kPdfExtensionId,
 #if BUILDFLAG(IS_CHROMEOS)
      extension_misc::kAssessmentAssistantExtensionId,
      extension_misc::kAccessibilityCommonExtensionId,
